== 考古研究机构 ==
奥斯曼帝国时期的最后一百年（19世纪）, 巴勒斯坦地区活跃的西方考古学家多数是基督徒, 受欧洲强国和教会支持。 随着奥斯曼帝国的统治被英国取代，考古学的政治性和宗教性减弱，历史性和科学性变得更强。一战和英国在巴勒斯坦的统治确定后，考古研究机构越来越多的集中在耶路撒冷.<ref name="yba">{{cite journal|url=http://www.ybz.org.il/_Uploads/dbsAttachedFiles/Article_92.6.pdf|last=Ben-Aryeh|first=Yehoshua|date=1999|journal=Cathedra|publisher=Yad Yitzhak Ben-Zvi|accessdate=2013-03-30|issue=92|language=he|script-title=he:המוסדות הזרים לארכאולוגיה ולחקירת ארץ־ישראל בתקופת המנדט|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206081713/http://www.ybz.org.il/_Uploads/dbsAttachedFiles/Article_92.6.pdf|archivedate=2015-02-06|deadurl=yes|trans_title=The Foreign Institutions of Archeology and Exploration of the Land of Israel During the British Mandate (Tammuz 1999)|df=}}</ref>{{Rp|135–136}}

 在1913年至1914年，Yishuv的知识精英成立了the Socity for the Reclamation of Antiquities。其创始人之一是Avraham Yaakov Brawer，David Yellin和Aharon Meir Mazie。该协会于1920年改名为犹太巴勒斯坦探索协会，后来改名为以色列探险协会。
耶路撒冷的英国考古学院在1921年开始运作，巴勒斯坦探矿基金会的斯图尔特·马卡利斯特和邓肯·麦肯齐先生呼吁英国政府建立一个当地文物当局。 Macalister和Mackenzie表示关注由于战斗在整个土地上战斗给考古遗址带来的危险。麦肯齐对警察考古遗址和偷窃物品也警惕 In 1913–1914 the Society for the Reclamation of Antiquities was established by the [[依舒夫|Yishuv]]'s intellectual elite. Among its founder were Avraham Yaakov Brawer, David Yellin and Aharon Meir Mazie. The Society changed its name to the Jewish Palestine Exploration Society in 1920 and later to the Israel Exploration Society.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.haaretz.com/weekend/week-s-end/israel-s-archeological-triumphs-through-the-eyes-of-a-man-who-was-always-there.premium-1.512460|title=Israel's archeological triumphs through the eyes of a man who was always there|last=Hasson|first=Nir|date=2013-03-29|newspaper=[[Haaretz|Haaretz]]|accessdate=2013-03-30|archive-date=2013-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130330062520/http://www.haaretz.com/weekend/week-s-end/israel-s-archeological-triumphs-through-the-eyes-of-a-man-who-was-always-there.premium-1.512460|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://israelexplorationsociety.huji.ac.il/ies.html|title=About the Israel Exploration Society|accessdate=2013-03-30|publisher=[[Israel_Exploration_Society|Israel Exploration Society]]|archive-date=2013-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130305092026/http://israelexplorationsociety.huji.ac.il/ies.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
