== 考古学政治化 ==
''更多信息'': Politics of archaeology in Israel and Palestine

Archaeological research and preservation efforts have been exploited by both Palestinians and Israelis for partisan ends.<ref name="Adam">{{cite web|url=http://www.hsrcpress.ac.za/downloadpdf.php?pdffile=files%2FPDF%2F2016%2F2016_00_Peacemaking_in_Divided_Societies.pdf&downloadfilename=Peace-Making%20in%20Divided%20Societies%20-%20Peace-making%20in%20Divided%20Societies%20-%20Entire%20eBook|title=Peace-Making in Divided Societies – The Israel-South Africa Analogy|accessdate=2011-07-12|last=Heibert|first=Adam|year=2002|format=PDF|publisher=Human Sciences Research Council Publishers|issn=1684-2839|location=Cape Town, South Africa|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924031632/http://www.hsrcpress.ac.za/downloadpdf.php?pdffile=files%2FPDF%2F2016%2F2016_00_Peacemaking_in_Divided_Societies.pdf&downloadfilename=Peace-Making%20in%20Divided%20Societies%20-%20Peace-making%20in%20Divided%20Societies%20-%20Entire%20eBook|archive-date=2015-09-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>Rather than attempting to understand "the natural process of [[拆除|demolition]], eradication, rebuilding, evasion, and ideological reinterpretation that has permitted ancient rulers and modern groups to claim exclusive possession," archaeologists have instead become active participants in the battle over partisan memory, with the result that archaeology, a seemingly objective science, has exacerbated the ongoing [[民族主義|nationalist]] dispute. Silberman concludes: "The digging continues. Claims and counterclaims about exclusive historical 'ownership' weave together the random acts of violence of bifurcated collective memory." Adam and Moodley conclude their investigation into this issue by writing that, "Both sides remain prisoners of their mythologized past."<ref name="Adam" />

As an example of this process, an archaeological tunnel running the length of the western side of the [[圣殿山|Temple Mount]], as it is known to [[犹太人|Jews]], or the [[圣殿山|Haram al-Sharif]], as it is known to [[伊斯兰教|Muslims]], became a serious point of contestation in 1996. The tunnel had been in place for about a dozen years, but open conflict broke out after the government of [[本雅明·内塔尼亚胡|Benjamin Netanyahu]] decided to open a new entrance to the tunnel from the [[維亞多勒羅沙|Via Dolorosa]] in the Muslim quarter of the [[耶路撒冷旧城|Old City]]. Palestinians and the Islamic [[瓦合甫|Waqf]] authorities were outraged that the decision was taken without prior consultation. They claimed that the work threatened the foundations of the compound and those of houses in the Muslim quarter and that it was actually aimed at tunnelling under the holy compound complex to find remains of [[所罗门圣殿|Solomon's Temple]], similar to previous accusations in the 1980s. As a result of the rumor, Arabs rioted in Jerusalem and then spread to the West Bank, leading to the deaths of 86 Palestinians and 15 Israeli soldiers.<ref name="Ross">Ross, 2007, pp. 156–157.</ref>

== 对考古遗址的破坏 ==
[[File:1900s_Jerusalem_old_city.jpg|缩略图]]位于图片下方。两个大的穹顶，分别是胡瓦犹太会堂（Hurva Synagogue）和 [[荣耀以色列犹太会堂|Tiferes Yisrael Synagogue]], 两个会堂在1948年被约旦军队摧毁。]]
1948–1967年，约旦当局和军队参与了对耶路撒冷老城犹太区的“精心策划的摧毁”。 <ref name="UNISPAL">{{Cite web|url=http://domino.un.org/UNISPAL.nsf/85255a0a0010ae82852555340060479d/a8138ad15b0fcac385256b920059debf!OpenDocument|title=Letter dated 5 March 1968 from the permanent Representative of Israel to the United Nations addressed to the Secretary-General|accessdate=2008-02-19|date=1968-03-06|publisher=[[United_Nations|United Nations]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070216154111/http://domino.un.org/unispal.nsf/85255a0a0010ae82852555340060479d/a8138ad15b0fcac385256b920059debf%21OpenDocument|archivedate=2007-02-16|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 在以色列驻联合国代表Yosef Tekoa写给联合国的信中，他抗议约旦“恶意毁坏、亵渎和侵犯”的政策 ，老城内除了一处会堂外，所有犹太会堂被炸毁或被作为马厩。<ref name="Gold">Gold, 2007, p. 157</ref> 通往橄榄山犹太人墓地的道路被切断，上万块犹太人墓碑，一些追溯到公元前一世纪，被毁坏或作为石板、台阶、和建筑材料修建约旦军事设施。<ref>{{Cite book|title=A History of Israel: from the Rise of Zionism to our Time|url=https://archive.org/details/historyofisraelf0000sach_y2a2|last=Sachar|first=Howard M.|authorlink=Howard Sachar|publisher=Alfred A Knopf|year=2007|isbn=978-0-375-71132-9|edition=3rd|location=New York, NY|page=[https://archive.org/details/historyofisraelf0000sach_y2a2/page/436 436]|quote=...a road was cut through the Jewish cemetery on the Mount of Olives, and the headstones of Jewish graves there were used for building purposes, some of them footpaths to army latrines.}}</ref>

1982年，在约旦国提议下，老城和老城城墙被列入处于危险的世界遗产名录。<ref name="WHS">{{Cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/archive/repcom82.htm#jerusalem|title=United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, Convention Concerning the Protestion of the World Cultural and Natural Heritage|accessdate=2008-02-20|date=1983-01-17|publisher=[[UNESCO|UNESCO]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080316130827/http://whc.unesco.org/archive/repcom82.htm#jerusalem|archivedate=2008-03-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

自1990年代后期，Islamic Waqf在圣殿山上将两个古代地下结构改造为一个清真寺的工程毁坏了所罗门马厩和  [[户勒大门|Huldah Gates]] 区域的考古遗址。<ref name="Shanks">{{Cite web|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB118472091594669763.html?mod=opinion&ojcontent=otep|title=Opinion:Biblical Destruction|accessdate=2008-02-19|date=2008-07-18|last=Hershel Shanks|publisher=Wall Street Journal|archive-date=2012-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108055757/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB118472091594669763.html?mod=opinion&ojcontent=otep|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Chabin">{{Cite web|url=http://www.juf.org/news/israel.aspx?id=10300|title=Archaeologists Campaign to Stop Desecration of Temple Mount|accessdate=2008-02-19|date=2006-07-11|last=Michele Chabin|publisher=[[Jewish_United_Fund|Jewish United Fund]]|archive-date=2011-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717200255/http://www.juf.org/news/israel.aspx?id=10300|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Amiel">{{Cite web|url=http://www.jcpa.org/jl/vp483.htm|title=The Destruction of the Temple Mount Antiquities|accessdate=2008-02-19|date=2002-08-01|last=Mark Ami-El|publisher=[[Jerusalem_Center_for_Public_Affairs|Jerusalem Center for Public Affairs]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080303140138/http://www.jcpa.org/jl/vp483.htm|archivedate=2008-03-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>

第一圣殿时期的遗址被毁坏，上千吨挖掘出的古代fill被倾倒进 [[汲沦谷|Kidron Valley]] 和耶路撒冷市政垃圾堆。这使得进行考古学调查变得不可能。

2011年，以色列发表年报，批评Waqf在圣殿山上的翻新工程。这一工程没有得到许可，并使用了工程机械，对考古遗址造成了破坏。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/national/waqf-temple-mount-excavation-damaged-archaeological-relics-1.362332 |title='Waqf Temple Mount excavation damaged archaeological relics' |accessdate=2017-03-04 |archive-date=2015-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502120216/http://www.haaretz.com/news/national/waqf-temple-mount-excavation-damaged-archaeological-relics-1.362332 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2012年，贝都因挖宝者毁坏了Beit Shemesh附近的一个十字军建筑下的一个两千年历史的古井的围墙。 .<ref>[http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4173467,00.html "Gold diggers ravage archeological site"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4173467,00.html |date=20170319220205 }}, ''Ynetnews''</ref>

